Security Manager

Kimbell Art Museum is seeking a manager to assume responsibility for
operations of the security department and assist in the development of the
security system for the future Kimbell building.? Qualifications include
development and implementation of security and safety and fire prevention
policies, procedures, and programs to safeguard the collection, staff,
visitors, building, and grounds.? Position requires demonstrated personnel
management ability; aptitude to develop and manage budgets; ability to pass
Texas Private Security Board Qualified Manger test and maintain Letter of
Authority and all employee state certifications; experience of five or more
years in the management of a security department for a like-sized
institution; previous experience or knowledge of security surveillance
systems; ability to work with staff members at all levels; strong written
and oral communication skills; and a Bachelor?s degree.? Candidates should
submit a letter of application, resume, and professional references to
Kimbell Art Museum, Human Resources, 3333 Camp Bowie Boulevard, Fort Worth,
TX 76107.
agrimes@kimbellmuseum.org




